HEADWORD: Paleolithic
<hw>Pa`le*o*lith"ic</hw>
<pr>(p⟦amac⟧`l⟦esl⟧*⟦osl⟧*l⟦icr⟧th"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to an era marked by early stone
implements. The <xex>Paleolithic</xex> era (as proposed by Lubbock)
includes the earlier half of the ⟦ldquo⟧Stone Age;⟦rdquo⟧ the remains
belonging to it are for the most part of extinct animals, with relics of
human beings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paleologist</ent>⟦br⟧
